(50, 1, 1, 47, 1, 1, 1, 'Paul and Timotheus', 'Connection of Paul and Timothy', 'Both passages emphasize the partnership of Paul and Timothy in ministry. They address specific churches, highlighting their roles as servants and brothers in Christ.', 'parallel', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 1, 44, 16, 12, 15, 'servants of Jesus Christ', 'Connection Between Paul and Philippi', 'This connection highlights Paul''s role as a servant of Jesus Christ in both passages. In Philippians, he addresses the saints in Christ Jesus at Philippi, while in Acts, he establishes the church there by preaching to Lydia and others.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 1, 45, 1, 1, 1, 'servants of Jesus Christ', 'Servants of Jesus Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Paul as a servant of Jesus Christ. This connection highlights the shared identity of Paul in his ministry and mission.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 1, 51, 1, 1, 2, 'the saints in Christ Jesus', 'Connection Between Philippians and Colossians', 'Both passages address ''the saints'' in specific locations, emphasizing their shared identity in Christ. Additionally, both letters are co-authored by Paul and Timotheus, highlighting their collaborative ministry.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 1, 45, 1, 7, 7, 'saints in Christ Jesus', 'Connection of Saints in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''saints'' in their respective communities. Philippians addresses ''all the saints in Christ Jesus,'' while Romans speaks to ''called to be saints,'' highlighting a shared identity among believers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 1, 46, 1, 1, 2, 'saints in Christ Jesus', 'Connection of Saints in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''saints in Christ Jesus.'' This connection highlights the communal aspect of believers in different locations, as both letters address groups of Christians identified as saints.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 1, 49, 1, 1, 1, 'saints in Christ Jesus', 'Connection of Saints in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize ''saints in Christ Jesus,'' highlighting a shared identity among believers in different locations. This connection underscores the unity of the Christian community as seen in both Philippi and Ephesus.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 2, 45, 1, 7, 7, NULL, 'Grace and Peace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the greeting of grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. This thematic parallel highlights a common introduction in the letters of Paul.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 2, 47, 1, 2, 2, 'Grace be unto you, and peace', 'Shared Greeting Formula', 'Both passages emphasize a common greeting of grace and peace from God and Jesus. This connection highlights the consistency in the apostolic letters'' opening salutations.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 2, 60, 1, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Grace and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize grace and peace as blessings from God. The similar phrasing in both verses highlights a shared theme of divine favor and tranquility offered to believers.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 3, 46, 1, 4, 4, 'I thank my God', 'Expressions of Gratitude', 'Both passages emphasize gratitude towards God for others. Philippians mentions remembrance, while Corinthians highlights thankfulness on behalf of others.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 3, 52, 1, 2, 3, 'I thank my God upon every remembrance of you', 'Expressions of Gratitude', 'Both passages emphasize giving thanks to God for the recipients. Philippians 1:3 mentions ''every remembrance of you,'' while 1 Thessalonians 1:2 highlights ''making mention of you in our prayers.'' This connection highlights a shared theme of gratitude in prayer.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 3, 57, 1, 4, 5, 'I thank my God', 'Expressions of Gratitude', 'Both passages emphasize gratitude towards God for others. Philippians expresses thanks upon remembrance, while Philemon mentions constant prayers of thanks for love and faith.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 3, 55, 1, 3, 3, 'remembrance of you', 'Expressions of Gratitude in Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize gratitude and remembrance in prayer. Philippians 1:3 mentions ''every remembrance of you,'' while 2 Timothy 1:3 speaks of ''remembrance of thee in my prayers night and day.''', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 3, 49, 1, 15, 16, 'I thank my God upon every remembrance of you', 'Expressions of Gratitude in Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize giving thanks to God for the believers. Philippians 1:3 expresses gratitude upon remembrance, while Ephesians 1:15-16 highlights ongoing thanks in prayer.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 3, 51, 1, 3, 4, 'I thank my God upon every remembrance of you', 'Expressions of Gratitude', 'Both passages emphasize giving thanks to God for the believers. Philippians expresses gratitude upon remembrance, while Colossians highlights ongoing prayers of thanks for their faith and love.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 3, 52, 3, 9, 9, 'I thank my God upon every remembrance of you', 'Expressions of Gratitude', 'Both passages emphasize gratitude towards God for the believers. Philippians 1:3 expresses thanks upon remembrance, while 1 Thessalonians 3:9 speaks of joy and thanks for their sake.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 4, 52, 1, 2, 2, NULL, 'Prayer and Thanksgiving Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of prayer and gratitude towards the recipients. They highlight a communal bond through consistent prayer, reflecting joy and thankfulness.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 4, 45, 1, 9, 9, 'always in every prayer of mine', 'Prayer and Joy Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer and the joy associated with it. Philippians mentions making requests with joy, while Romans highlights making mention of others in prayer without ceasing.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 4, 63, 1, 4, 4, 'with joy', 'Joy in Prayer and Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy in both passages. Philippians expresses joy in prayer, while 2 John emphasizes joy in witnessing children walking in truth.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 4, 50, 2, 2, 2, 'making request with joy', 'Joy and Unity in Prayer', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy in both passages. In Philippians 1:4, Paul expresses joy in prayer for the believers, while Philippians 2:2 calls for unity to fulfill that joy.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 4, 49, 1, 14, 23, NULL, 'Prayer and Thanksgiving Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of prayer and giving thanks for fellow believers. Philippians mentions making requests with joy in prayer, while Ephesians highlights ceasing not to give thanks in prayers for the saints.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 4, 50, 1, 9, 11, 'Always in every prayer of mine', 'Connection of Prayer and Love', 'This connection highlights the theme of prayer and its purpose in fostering love among the believers. In Philippians 1:4, Paul expresses joy in his prayers, which aligns with his prayer in verses 9-11 for their love to abound.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 4, 51, 2, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Joy in Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of joy in relation to the faith of the believers. Philippians 1:4 expresses joy in prayer for others, while Colossians 2:5 reflects joy in spiritual connection despite physical absence.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 5, 50, 4, 14, 15, 'fellowship in the gospel', 'Fellowship in the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the Philippians'' support and partnership in the gospel. The reference to ''fellowship in the gospel'' in the first passage connects to their unique role in communicating with Paul during his affliction.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 5, 50, 1, 7, 7, 'fellowship in the gospel', 'Fellowship in the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of partnership in the gospel. The mention of ''fellowship in the gospel'' in verse 5 connects to being ''partakers of my grace'' in verse 7, highlighting shared involvement in the faith.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 5, 57, 1, 17, 17, 'fellowship in the gospel', 'Partnership in the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the theme of partnership in the gospel. Both passages emphasize the importance of fellowship and receiving others as partners in the faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 5, 58, 3, 14, 14, 'from the first day until now', 'Fellowship and Confidence Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of perseverance in faith. Both passages emphasize the importance of maintaining a steadfast commitment from the beginning until the end.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 5, 44, 16, 12, 40, 'fellowship in the gospel', 'Fellowship in the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the establishment of the Philippian church through Paul''s ministry, as seen in Acts 16, where he and Silas engage with Lydia and the jailer, leading to their baptisms. Philippians 1:5 reflects on the ongoing fellowship and partnership in the gospel that began with these early converts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 5, 45, 15, 26, 26, 'fellowship in the gospel', 'Fellowship and Contribution Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of fellowship in supporting the needs of others. Both passages emphasize the importance of community involvement in the gospel and aiding the poor.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 5, 47, 8, 1, 1, 'fellowship in the gospel', 'Fellowship and Grace in Giving', 'This connection highlights the theme of fellowship and grace in the context of supporting the gospel. Both passages emphasize the importance of communal participation in the work of the gospel, with Philippians referencing fellowship and 2 Corinthians mentioning grace bestowed on churches.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 6, 19, 138, 8, 8, 'will perform it until the day', 'God''s Assurance of Completion', 'Both passages emphasize God''s commitment to completing His work in believers. Philippians 1:6 speaks of God performing a good work, while Psalms 138:8 assures that the Lord will perfect what concerns His people.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 6, 45, 8, 28, 30, 'good work in you', 'God''s Work in Believers', 'Both passages emphasize that God is actively working in the lives of believers. Philippians 1:6 states that God will perform a good work until the day of Jesus Christ, while Romans 8:28-30 assures that all things work together for good according to His purpose.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 6, 46, 1, 8, 8, 'good work in you', 'Confidence in God''s Work', 'Both passages emphasize God''s faithfulness in sustaining believers until the end. Philippians 1:6 assures that God will complete His work, while 1 Corinthians 1:8 speaks of being confirmed blameless at the day of Christ.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 6, 49, 4, 12, 12, 'good work in you', 'Work of God in Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the ongoing work of God in believers. Philippians 1:6 speaks of God completing His work, while Ephesians 4:12 describes the purpose of that work in perfecting the saints.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 6, 50, 2, 13, 13, 'good work in you', 'God''s Work in Believers', 'Both passages emphasize that God is actively working within believers. Philippians 1:6 assures that God will continue this good work, while Philippians 2:13 specifies that it is God who enables the will and actions aligned with His purpose.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 6, 52, 5, 23, 24, 'he which hath begun a good work in you', 'God''s Faithfulness in Sanctification', 'Both passages emphasize God''s commitment to completing the work He begins in believers. Philippians 1:6 assures that He will perform this work, while 1 Thessalonians 5:24 highlights His faithfulness in preserving believers until Christ''s return.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 6, 53, 1, 11, 11, 'good work in you', 'Connection of Good Work and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of God fulfilling His work in believers. Philippians speaks of God completing the good work He began, while 2 Thessalonians mentions fulfilling the work of faith with power.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 7, 47, 7, 3, 3, 'I have you in my heart', 'Shared Themes of Affection', 'Both passages emphasize the deep emotional connection the authors have with their communities, expressing a commitment to share in their struggles and joys. This connection highlights the idea of mutual support and partnership in faith.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 7, 50, 1, 5, 5, NULL, 'Fellowship in the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the shared commitment to the gospel. Philippians 1:5 highlights their fellowship, while Philippians 1:7 acknowledges their participation in his grace during his struggles.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 7, 51, 4, 18, 18, 'my bonds', 'Connection of Paul''s Bonds', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s bonds and grace. Philippians mentions his bonds in the context of sharing grace, while Colossians directly reminds the readers of his bonds.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 7, 55, 2, 9, 9, 'in my bonds', 'Suffering and the Gospel''s Freedom', 'Both passages emphasize suffering for the gospel. Philippians mentions being in bonds while defending the gospel, and 2 Timothy highlights suffering trouble yet asserts that the word of God is not bound.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 7, 44, 16, 23, 25, 'in my bonds', 'Connection of Suffering and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s experience in bonds and his reliance on God''s grace. In Philippians, he mentions being in bonds and partaking in grace, while Acts describes his imprisonment and prayerful response.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 7, 44, 20, 23, 23, 'bonds', 'Connection of Bonds and Afflictions', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of ''bonds'' and the suffering associated with the gospel. Philippians 1:7 mentions Paul''s bonds, while Acts 20:23 highlights that ''bonds and afflictions abide'' him, illustrating a shared experience of hardship in the ministry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 7, 49, 3, 1, 1, 'in my bonds', 'Connection of Paul''s Imprisonment', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s status as a prisoner. Philippians mentions his bonds, while Ephesians explicitly states he is a prisoner for the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 8, 45, 1, 9, 9, 'long after you all in the bowels of Jesus Christ', 'Expressions of Longing and Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize a deep emotional connection and commitment to prayer for others. Philippians expresses longing ''in the bowels of Jesus Christ,'' while Romans highlights ''without ceasing'' prayer for the recipients.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 8, 50, 4, 1, 1, NULL, 'Connection of Affection and Longing', 'Both passages emphasize the deep affection Paul has for the Philippians. The phrase ''longed for'' in both verses highlights his emotional connection and desire for their well-being.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 8, 52, 2, 8, 8, 'long after you all in the bowels', 'Affectionate Longing for Believers', 'Both passages emphasize a deep affection for the recipients. Philippians expresses longing ''in the bowels of Jesus Christ,'' while 1 Thessalonians speaks of being ''affectionately desirous'' and willing to share their own souls.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 8, 55, 1, 4, 4, 'long after you all', 'Expressions of Longing and Joy', 'Both passages emphasize a deep longing for others, with Philippians expressing a longing ''after you all'' and 2 Timothy highlighting a desire ''to see thee.'' This connection highlights the emotional bonds shared among believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 8, 45, 9, 1, 1, 'long after you all in the bowels', 'Expressions of Deep Affection', 'Both passages emphasize a deep longing and sincerity in the relationships Paul has with others. Philippians 1:8 expresses longing ''in the bowels of Jesus Christ,'' while Romans 9:1 conveys truthfulness and heartfelt witness ''in Christ.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 8, 51, 2, 1, 1, 'how greatly I long after you all', 'Apostolic Affection and Conflict', 'This connection highlights the deep emotional investment Paul has for the believers, as seen in his longing in Philippians and his conflict for them in Colossians. Both passages emphasize his care and concern for those he has not met personally.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 8, 24, 31, 20, 20, 'the bowels of Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Deep Affection', 'Both passages emphasize deep emotional longing and compassion. The phrase ''bowels'' in both contexts signifies a profound inner feeling of love and mercy towards others.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 9, 52, 3, 12, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Abounding Love', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of love abounding. Philippians 1:9 focuses on love increasing in knowledge and judgment, while 1 Thessalonians 3:12 highlights love increasing toward one another and all men.', 'theme', 0.6779999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 9, 51, 1, 9, 9, 'knowledge', 'Connection of Knowledge and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowledge and understanding in the context of love and spiritual growth. Philippians focuses on love abounding in knowledge and judgment, while Colossians highlights being filled with the knowledge of God''s will in wisdom and understanding.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 9, 61, 1, 5, 6, 'in knowledge', 'Connection of Knowledge and Virtue', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowledge as a foundation for growth in love and virtue. Philippians highlights love abounding in knowledge, while 2 Peter encourages adding knowledge to virtue, suggesting a progression in spiritual development.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 9, 57, 1, 6, 6, 'love may abound yet more and more', 'Connection of Love and Faith', 'This connection highlights the importance of love and faith in the believer''s life. Both passages emphasize the growth of love and the acknowledgment of good things in Christ, suggesting that love and faith are interconnected in the Christian experience.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 9, 51, 3, 10, 10, 'in knowledge', 'Connection of Knowledge and Renewal', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowledge in the growth of love and the renewal of the believer. Philippians highlights love abounding in knowledge, while Colossians speaks of being renewed in knowledge after the image of God.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 9, 47, 8, 7, 7, NULL, 'Abounding in Love and Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of abounding in love and knowledge. Philippians 1:9 focuses on love abounding in knowledge, while 2 Corinthians 8:7 encourages abounding in love and knowledge as part of grace.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 9, 60, 1, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection of Love in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love, urging believers to cultivate it with sincerity and depth. Philippians highlights love abounding in knowledge and judgment, while 1 Peter calls for fervent love with a pure heart.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 10, 45, 12, 2, 2, 'approve things that are excellent', 'Transformation and Approval of Excellence', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of discernment and transformation in the believer''s life. Philippians encourages believers to approve things that are excellent, while Romans calls for a renewal of the mind to prove God''s will.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 10, 52, 3, 13, 13, 'without offence till the day of Christ', 'Holiness and Sincerity at Christ''s Coming', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being sincere and unblameable in holiness until the coming of Christ. They highlight the need for believers to maintain a pure and excellent character as they await His return.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
