(50, 1, 10, 45, 2, 18, 18, 'approve things that are excellent', 'Connection of Approving Excellence', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of approving things that are excellent. Philippians 1:10 speaks of approving excellent things for sincerity, while Romans 2:18 refers to approving more excellent things through instruction from the law.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 10, 49, 5, 10, 10, 'approve things that are excellent', 'Connection of Approving and Accepting', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of discerning what is excellent and acceptable in the sight of God. Philippians encourages believers to approve things that are excellent, while Ephesians speaks to proving what is acceptable unto the Lord.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 10, 62, 4, 1, 1, 'approve things that are excellent', 'Testing Spiritual Authenticity', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of discernment. Philippians encourages believers to approve what is excellent, while 1 John urges them to try the spirits to identify true prophets. This connection highlights the need for sincerity and careful evaluation in faith.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 10, 50, 1, 6, 6, 'till the day of Christ', 'Confidence in God''s Work', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of being prepared and sincere until the day of Christ. Philippians 1:10 speaks of being sincere until that day, while Philippians 1:6 assures that God will continue His good work in believers until the same day.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 11, 58, 12, 11, 11, 'fruits of righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Chastening', 'Both passages emphasize the ''fruit of righteousness'' that results from spiritual processes. Philippians speaks of being filled with this fruit through Christ, while Hebrews discusses how chastening ultimately yields this same fruit.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 11, 43, 15, 8, 8, 'fruits of righteousness', 'Connection of Fruitfulness and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of bearing fruit as a demonstration of discipleship and righteousness. The ''fruits of righteousness'' in Philippians are linked to glorifying God, similar to how bearing ''much fruit'' in John glorifies the Father.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 11, 51, 1, 10, 10, 'fruits of righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Fruitfulness', 'Both passages emphasize being fruitful in good works and righteousness. They highlight the importance of living in a way that pleases God and reflects His glory.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 11, 48, 5, 22, 23, 'fruits of righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Fruit', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''fruits'' in both passages, where Philippians speaks of ''fruits of righteousness'' and Galatians lists the ''fruit of the Spirit.'' Both emphasize the importance of spiritual outcomes that glorify God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 11, 50, 4, 17, 17, 'fruits of righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Fruit', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''fruit'' in relation to righteousness and spiritual growth. Philippians 1:11 speaks of being filled with the ''fruits of righteousness,'' while Philippians 4:17 refers to ''fruit that may abound'' for the believers'' account.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 11, 59, 3, 17, 18, 'fruits of righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''fruits of righteousness'' and link it to peace. Philippians speaks of being filled with these fruits, while James notes that the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 11, 23, 61, 11, 11, 'fruits of righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness and Praise', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of righteousness and its relation to praise. Philippians speaks of being filled with the fruits of righteousness, while Isaiah describes righteousness and praise springing forth before the nations.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 12, 55, 2, 9, 9, 'furtherance of the gospel', 'Suffering and the Gospel''s Advancement', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering for the gospel. Both passages emphasize that despite personal trials, the message of God continues to spread.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 12, 45, 8, 28, 28, 'furtherance of the gospel', 'Purpose in Adversity', 'Both passages emphasize that circumstances, even difficult ones, contribute to a greater purpose. Philippians highlights the furtherance of the gospel, while Romans assures that all things work together for good.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 12, 44, 11, 19, 21, 'furtherance of the gospel', 'Furtherance of the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the spread of the gospel despite persecution. Philippians highlights how Paul''s circumstances advanced the gospel, while Acts describes how persecution led to the preaching of Jesus in new regions.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 12, 45, 8, 37, 37, 'furtherance of the gospel', 'Victory Through Adversity', 'This connection highlights the theme of overcoming challenges for the sake of the gospel. Both passages emphasize that difficulties can lead to triumph and further the mission of faith.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(50, 1, 12, 44, 8, 4, 4, 'furtherance of the gospel', 'Advancement of the Gospel', 'This connection highlights how both passages emphasize the spread of the gospel despite challenges. In Philippians, Paul notes that his circumstances have led to the furtherance of the gospel, while Acts describes how those scattered preached the word.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
