(50, 1, 12, 19, 76, 10, 10, 'furtherance of the gospel', 'Wrath and Furtherance of Gospel', 'This connection highlights how both passages address the idea that adverse circumstances can lead to positive outcomes. In Philippians, the ''things which happened unto me'' serve to advance the gospel, while in Psalms, ''the wrath of man shall praise thee'' suggests that human wrath can also contribute to divine purposes.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
